## HashMap.has() method

Returns a boolean asserting whether a value has been associated to the `key` in the map or not.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
has(key: K): boolean;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  key | K | The key of the element to test for presence in the hash map. |

<b>Returns:</b>

boolean
